text:
Yesterday, I paid an e-visit to the teams handling our COVID-19 testing efforts. Testing is a critical part of our strategy to control COVID-19, and the teams have been busy organising and running this.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
This huge and complicated operation depends on many individuals all doing their part so that the testing runs smoothly. It is not just getting the swab done, but being on the front line, taking all the precautions and doing the procedures right. It is hard work and I thank all of you who are making this possible.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
As we start Phase 2 of our re-opening on 19 June, we are also ramping up testing capacity so that we can safely and progressively resume work and social activities in the COVID world.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
To win this battle, we need everyone to continue doing our part by practising safe distancing and good personal hygiene. Let us make a safe and steady transition to Phase 2! â€“ LHL

image_desc: Photo by Lee Hsien Loong on August 13, 2020.
text:
Very happy to welcome Japan Foreign Minister Motegi Toshimitsu to the Istana today â€” he is my first foreign visitor since the pandemic led to entry restrictions and border closures. We had a good discussion on how we can do more together as we deal with the pandemic.

Japan is one of the countries with whom we are discussing setting up reciprocal â€˜green lanesâ€™, to resume essential travel with the necessary safety precautions. We are proceeding cautiously, as COVID-19 is still very much a threat. But this will be an important step forward in restoring connectivity between countries, and adjusting to life with COVID-19. â€“ LHL
 
(MCI Photos by Zinkie Aw)

image_desc: Photo by Lee Hsien Loong on August 20, 2020.
text:
Welcomed another foreign visitor to the Istana today. Despite the ongoing pandemic, itâ€™s a good feeling to return to some semblance of normalcy.
 
Had a fruitful meeting with Communist Party of China Politburo member and Central Commission for Foreign Affairs Office Director Yang Jiechi. As you would expect, we discussed our respective COVID-19 situations. Despite the pandemic, both sides have kept up contacts through phone and video calls. Singapore and China had earlier agreed on a â€œfast laneâ€ for essential business and official travel between both countries. At the moment this covers six Chinese provinces and municipalities, and hopefully this list will grow if the situation stays under control.

This year marks the 30th anniversary of Singapore-China diplomatic relations. Our ties with China are substantial and multi-faceted. I am confident that by working with each other and with the international community, we can make more progress in the post-COVID world. â€“ LHL
 
(MCI Photo by Lee Jia Wen)

text:
Happy to receive Indonesian Foreign Minister @retno_marsudi at the Istana this afternoon.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
I have spoken to President @jokowi several times in the past few months, and I continued the discussion with Minister Retno on jointly overcoming the pandemic. Singapore is glad to have been able to contribute medical supplies to support Indonesiaâ€™s fight against COVID-19. We are on track to remain the top foreign investor in Indonesia this year, as has been the case since 2014.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
Even as we pick up the pieces from the pandemic, we should not neglect helping each other recover from this crisis. As close neighbours, we have a responsibility to look out for each other, as we are all stronger together. â€“ LHL
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
(MCI Photo by Zinkie Aw)

text:
Gave my first speech of this Parliament this afternoon. Each first Parliament sitting is a valuable opportunity to take stock of how we have done so far, what has gotten us here, and what our immediate priorities are.
â €
This time, our work is cut out for us â€“ not only to deal with the immediate threat of COVID-19, but also to plan for an uncertain new future in its wake. â €
â €
In this climate of economic uncertainty, it is only natural to feel anxious about our social support, and competition from foreigners. I want to reassure Singaporeans that the Government will always be on your side. This is why we are adjusting our work pass schemes, and tightening the Fair Consideration Framework. However, please remember that we must stay open to the world, to attract businesses to set up here, and in turn create good jobs and opportunities for Singaporeans. â €
â €
During the clarifications, I explained the mindset we should have in elections. Voters are choosing the party they wish to govern Singapore; your vote matters. Vote because you truly support the party, whether PAP or opposition, and not because you want â€˜the best of both worldsâ€™. â €
â €
Singaporean voters have spoken, and I respect their choice. The Government will do its part to work with the opposition to keep Parliament a constructive forum for debate. â €
â €
Singapore has survived many life or death crises before. Each time we survived, and came back stronger. Like all previous crises, COVID-19 will be the occasion for us to do better, emerge stronger, and more united than before. 
â €
You can watch my full speech on the PMO YouTube channel (click on the link in my profile). â€“ LHLâ €
â €
(PMO Video by Alex Qiu & Chiez How)

image_desc: Photo by Lee Hsien Loong on October 02, 2020. May be an image of 2 people, people standing, suit and outerwear.
text:
Today marks 30 years of diplomatic relations between Singapore and China. Our relationship started even before formal establishment of diplomatic ties in 1990, and our bilateral collaboration has deepened and expanded over the years.
Â 
China has been our largest trading partner and we have been Chinaâ€™s largest foreign investor since 2013. People-to-people exchanges have also grown. In 2018 more than four million people travelled between our countries â€“ 40 times as many as the 100,000 travellers in 1990. COVID-19 has suspended the flights for now, but amid the pandemic, we have continued to support each other, and embarked on new areas of cooperation. Beyond bilateral ties, we have also worked well together in regional and international fora.
Â 
I look forward to growing and strengthening our ties and bringing our partnership to greater heights. â€“ LHL

(Premier Li Keqiang made an official visit to Singapore in November 2018. / MCI Photo by LH Goh)

A message from @ongyekung to our friends in Hong Kong!
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
The Singapore-Hong Kong Air Travel Bubble takes off next Sunday, 22 November, with the start of daily â€˜bubbleâ€™ flights between our two cities.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
Officials from both sides have worked hard to put in place measures to allow air travel to resume safely. Travellers will have to get used to new regulations and COVID-19 swab tests â€“ all part and parcel of the new normal.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
We are proceeding cautiously, but if the arrangement is successful and the pandemic continues to stay under control on both sides, we can look forward to expanding the bubble to more flights, and hopefully, to more destinations as well. â€“ LHLâ €â €â €â €â €â €â €
